    "here, H s = reconstructed HSI, H s = ground truth HSI.",
    "3.3.4.1 HSCNN+ Two advanced CNN-based hyperspectral reconstruction architectures are presented combinedly as HSCNN+ (Shi et al. 2018).",
    "Firstly, the development of a residual network named HSCNN-R is undertaken, consisting of a series of residual blocks.",
    "The model's superior performance stems from its contemporary architectural design and optimization achieved by eliminating hand-crafted image upsampling as seen in HSCNN.",
    "Building upon the promising results of HSCNN-R, another distinct architecture is introduced, wherein the residual blocks are replaced by dense blocks featuring a novel fusion scheme."
